25/01/2006
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- The death toll in the Monday (23 January) train crash in Montenegro reached 45 on Tuesday, as rescuers worked around the clock to remove victims from the rubble. Some 198 people were injured in the accident, 50 of them very seriously, the chief of the hospital in Podgorica said. Investigators were said to be focusing on brake failure or human error as the most likely reasons for the crash. A three-day mourning period was announced across Serbia-Montenegro on Tuesday. (Danas - 25/01/06; OSCE Web site, Reuters, AP, AFP - 24/01/06)
